25/10/2005
WASHINGTON, United States -- Macedonian Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski called on the United States Monday (24 October) to continue actively supporting his country and its aspirations for membership in NATO and the EU. 
Buckovski met with Secretary of State Condoleezza Rice and later with World Bank President Paul Wolfowitz.
In other news, media reports in Skopje suggest that the trial of former Interior Minister Ljube Boskovski and former security official Johan Tarculovski will begin on 18 December at the UN war crimes tribunal in The Hague. 
The two are charged with crimes committed during a police raid on the village Ljuboten in August 2001. 
(Macedonian Government Web site, Makfax - 25/10/05; A1 TV - 24/10/05)
